Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c\n+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c\n@@ -3257,10 +3257,18 @@\n     if (initialised) {\n-        wrefresh(stdscr);\n-        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);\n+        if (stdscr == NULL) {\n+            PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n+            return NULL;\n+        }\n+        wrefresh(stdscr);\n+        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);\n     }\n-\n-    win = initscr();\n-\n-    if (win == NULL) {\n-        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n-        return NULL;\n-    }\n-\n-    initialised = initialised_setupterm = TRUE;\n+    win = initscr();\n+    if (win == NULL) {\n+        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n+        return NULL;\n+    }\n+    initialised = initialised_setupterm = TRUE;\n'}`
responded: The ASAN report shows the crash moved to:

```
    - _curses_initscr_impl Modules/_cursesmodule.c:3262:9
```

That is:
```c
3262|     win = initscr();
```

And soon after:
```c
3267|     }
3268|
3269|     initialised = initialised_setupterm = TRUE;
```

**Root cause:**
- If `initscr()` returns `NULL`, we handle it (`win == NULL`) and return with an error.
- But _afterwards_, we set `initialised = TRUE`, regardless of whether initialization was successful.
- On the next call to `_curses_initscr_impl`, `if (initialised)` block is entered—even though `stdscr` is not set (is NULL). Then we crash on using `stdscr`.

**Proper fix:**
- Only set `initialised=initialised_setupterm=TRUE` after a successful call to `initscr` that returns a valid window pointer.
- And in the `if (initialised)` block, check `stdscr` as previously patched.

Here is the revised patch:

```diff
--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
@@ -3257,10 +3257,18 @@
     if (initialised) {
-        wrefresh(stdscr);
-        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
+        if (stdscr == NULL) {
+            PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
+            return NULL;
+        }
+        wrefresh(stdscr);
+        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
     }

-    win = initscr();
-
-    if (win == NULL) {
-        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
-        return NULL;
-    }
-
-    initialised = initialised_setupterm = TRUE;
+    win = initscr();
+    if (win == NULL) {
+        PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
+        return NULL;
+    }
+    initialised = initialised_setupterm = TRUE;
```

This ensures that the module considers itself initialized only if curses initialization actually worked (i.e., `initscr()` did not return `NULL`). Let's validate this patch.

